places.adrFormatAddress: No. 340-9, DunHua N Rd, Songshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10548

editorialSummary.text: Commercial airport & military airbase with domestic flights & service to China, South Korea & Japan.

places.formattedAddress: No. 340-9, DunHua N Rd, Songshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10548
places.name: places/ChIJWSYUpPGrQjQROop1ttwNGJM

originalText.text:
A very compact airport where you can take flights for domestic travel in Taiwan. It's clean and practical. They also sell braised dishes and have a 7/11 in the boarding area, which is very convenient for passengers. :)

I also love the beautiful view of the planes taking off!

text.text:
A very compact airport where you can take flights for domestic travel in Taiwan. It's clean and practical. They also sell braised dishes and have a 7/11 in the boarding area, which is very convenient for passengers. :)

I also love the beautiful view of the planes taking off!

originalText.text:
Former international airport for Taiwan.
Now it mainly serves domestic flights. However there are some international flights still used in SongShan Airport.
There is a foodcourt at level 2 of domestic flight terminal, and the food tastes great.
There are also some stalls available selling cookies, domestic stuff at level 1.
Mainly 3 main airlines served in the domestic flight.

originalText.text: Visited here for International flights. The only good thing about this airport is its location. Other than that, you will feel like traveling domestic flights. Shops, restaurants, facilities need to be much more improved + The lounge at International Departure is poor and I recommend that you use Taoyuan Airport even it takes much more time for better experience.
